HEADWORD: Horse Guards
<hw>Horse" Guards`</hw> <pr>(h⟦ocir⟧rs"g⟦aum⟧rdz`)</pr>.
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A body of cavalry so called; esp., a British
regiment, called the Royal Horse Guards, which furnishes guards of state
for the sovereign.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>The Horse Guards</b></col>, <cd>a name given to the
former headquarters of the commander in chief of the British army, at
Whitehall in London.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Horsehair</ent>⟦br⟧
